reviews.review:
Beautful game, excellent story, great gameplay.  Good stuff.  Worth your money.

Could it have been better?  Probably.  Some of the plot twists are a little off-balance, and the ending is a bit rough (to say the least).  Playing through the [i] Burial at Sea [/i] expansion will largely round off these rough edges and is therefore required if you ever want to experience the actual ending to the Bioshock series.

[i] Clash in the Clouds [/i] is pure trash, finely-ground.  It's single-player horde mode, basically.  Not my cup of tea.  I wouldn't have minded it so much except that it has achievements (grindy, grindy achievements) which make 100%-ing the game far more aggravating than it neccesarily needs to be.

{{
If you're one of those types who care about achievements, here's some sage-like advice: play through the game first, without consulting any guides or even checking your earned / un-earned achievement list.  
I did not do this, and found myself throwing away my favorite weapons mid-game, or limiting myself to wimpy Vigors solely because it was required to do so in order to get one of those precious 'chieves'.  It really cuts into your enjoyment of the game.  Fair warning.
}}

Overall a great game, a fantastic story, and a definite candidate for one of the top ten best games of all time.
